      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating Costs</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Free application doesn't mean cheap destination. Aruba is one of the more expensive Caribbean islands. Budget $2,500+/month minimum.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Staying Only in Tourist Zones</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Eagle Beach and Palm Beach areas are beautiful but expensive. Look at Oranjestad, Noord, or other local neighborhoods for better long-term value.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Forgetting the ED Card</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The $15 Embarkation/Disembarkation card is required for entry—separate from the workation application. Complete it before travel.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Not Checking Internet First</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">While generally good, internet quality varies by property. Verify speeds before booking long-term accommodation.</p>
      </div>

